dismissalText.commentary: Hashan Tillakaratne run out (ME Waugh) 25 (26b 1x4 0x6 54m) SR: 96.15

notes: RS Kaluwitharana was named the Player of the Preliminary Series prior to the start of the match.
Aus 50 off 11.3 ov; 100 off 19.1 ov; 150 off 27.4 ov; 200 off 40.4 ov; 250 off 47.4 ov.
ME Waugh - 50 off 55 balls Taylor - 50 off 63 balls
de Silva was injured with a bleeding hand when he dropped Healy (11) in the 46th over, off the bowling of Jayasuriya. M Muralitharan substituted for the remainder of the innings.
Ranatunga dropped Healy (13) in the first ball of the 47th over bowled by Vaas.
Vaas dropped Healy (30) off his own bowling in the 49th over
Australian score is the 4th highest ODI total in Sydney
Heavy rain during the tea break delayed the start of Sri Lanka's innings. Target was readjusted to 168 in 25 overs (167 would be an Australian win).
Jayasuriya (12) was dropped by Reiffel in the 3rd over off McGrath's bowling.
Ranatunga (20) survived a caught and bowled chance in the 16th over by Reiffel.
Jayasuriya was a runner for Ranatunga from the 18th over, having been denied to do so by umpire Randell in the previous over.
Match finished at 10:58pm (scheduled finishing time was 10:30pm)
